<p>I’ve recently found the best Emacs package ever: <a href="https://github.com/dunn/company-emoji">company-emoji</a>.  It’s a
<a href="http://company-mode.github.io">Company</a> source for Emoji input 😍.</p>

<!--more-->

<figure>
<img alt="Animation showning emoji input with Company" src="/images/company-emoji.gif" />
<figcaption>Emoji input with Company</figcaption>
</figure>

<p>Just install from MELPA, enable it with <code class="highlighter-rouge">(add-to-list 'company-backends
'company-emoji)</code> and enjoy 😍 👍</p>